6. Running Containers
=====================


To run a container use below command:
-------------------------------------
sytnax:
docker container run <image name> 
eg:
$ docker container run hello-world     or   docker run hello-world

To list docker images present on you local system:
--------------------------------------------------
$ docker images 
$ docker image ls


To run a ubuntu container and access its bash using below command:
------------------------------------------------------------------
syntax:
$docker container run -it --name python-container <imagename or image ID>

-i option is used for interactive 
-t option is used for psuedo tty terminal 
--name option is used to specify a name to container so it is easy to find out

eg:
docker container run -it --name python-container <imagename or image ID>







